description: Set when NEMA Phase On becomes active, either upon start of green or walk interval, whichever occurs first.
Set when either solid or flashing green indication has begun. Do not set repeatedly during flashing operation.
Set when a conflicting call is registered against the active phase. (Marks beginning of MAX timing)
Set when phase min timer expires.
Phase termination due to gap out termination condition. Set once per phase when phase gaps out but may not necessarily occur upon phase termination.
Set when phase MAX timer expires but may not necessarily occur upon phase termination due to last car passage or other features.
Set when phase force off is applied by the coordinator to the active green phase.
Set when phase green indications are terminated into either yellow change interval or permissive (FYA) movement.
Set when phase yellow indication becomes active and interval timer begins.
Set when phase yellow indication becomes inactive.
Set only if phase red clearance is served. Set when red clearance timing begins.

Set only if phase red clearance is served. Set when red clearance timing concludes. This may not necessarily coincide with completion of the phase, especially during clearance of trailing overlaps, red revert timing, red rest, or delay for other ring terminations.
Set when the phase is no longer active within the ring, including completion of any trailing overlaps or end of barrier delays for adjacent ring termination.
Set when phase extension timer gaps out.
Set when phase in the programmed ring is skipped for any reason.
Set when extension timer starts to reduce (the time before reduction).
Set when extension timer minimum is reached (after the time to reduce).
Set when phase added initial timer expires.
Set when the controller determines a phase will be next to begin green after the current active phase(s) end red clearance.
Set when TSP early force off is applied to an active phase.
Set when controller applies preemption force off to the active cycle.
Set when walk indication becomes active.
Set when flashing don’t walk indication becomes active.
Set when don’t walk indication becomes solid (non-flashing) from either termination of pedestrian change interval, or head illumination after a pedestrian dark interval.
Set when the pedestrian outputs are set off.

Set when extended pedestrian change interval is requested by pressing the pedestrian push button for two (2) seconds. See 2009 MUTCD Section 4E.13 - Accessible Pedestrian Signals and Detectors - Extended Pushbutton Press Features for more details.
Set when pedestrian phase is active beyond pedestrian change interval or force off point.
Set when all active phases become inactive in the ring and cross barrier phases are next to be served.
Set when flashing yellow arrow becomes active.
Set when flashing yellow arrow becomes inactive through either clearance of the permissive movement or transition into a protected movement.
Set when phase hold is applied by the coordinator, preemptor, or external logic. Phase does not necessarily need to be actively timing for this event to occur.
Set when phase hold is released by the coordinator, preemptor, or external logic. Phase does not necessarily need to be actively timing for this event to occur.
Call to service on a phase is registered by vehicular demand. This event will not be set if a recall exists on the phase.
Call to service on a phase is cleared by either service of the phase or removal of call.
Call to service on a phase is registered by pedestrian demand. This event will not be set if a recall exists on the phase.

Set when phase omit is applied by the coordinator, preemptor, or other dynamic sources. Phase does not necessarily need to be actively timing for this event to occur. This event is not set when phase is removed from the active sequence or other configuration-level change has occurred.

Set when phase omit is released by the coordinator, preemptor, or other dynamic sources. Phase does not necessarily need to be actively timing for this event to occur. This event is not set when phase is added from the active sequence or other configuration-level change has occurred.

Set when pedestrian omit is applied by the coordinator, preemptor, or other dynamic sources. Phase does not necessarily need to be actively timing for this event to occur. This event is not set when phase is removed from the active sequence or other configuration-level change has occurred.

Set when pedestrian omit is released by the coordinator, preemptor, or other dynamic sources. Phase does not necessarily need to be actively timing for this event to occur. This event is not set when phase is added from the active sequence or other configuration-level change has occurred.
Set when maximum green (MAX 1) interval is in-effect for the active phase.
Set when maximum green (MAX 2) interval is in-effect for the active phase.
Set when dynamic max interval is in-effect for the active phase. This event shall be populated upon termination of MAX green (MAX 1 or MAX 2) interval.
Set when dynamic max interval steps up for the active phase (initially after two consecutive phase max out events).
Set when dynamic max interval steps down for the active phase (initially after two consecutive phase gap out events).
Set when advance warning sign is on.
Set when advance warning sign is off.

Set when overlap becomes green. Do not set repeatedly when overlap is flashing green. Note that overlap colors are consistent to the GYR intervals resultant from the controller programming and may not be indicative of actual signal head colors.
Set when overlap is green and extension timers begin timing.

Set when overlap is in a yellow change interval state.
 Note that overlaps which drive yellow field indications during a dwell state may be reported as green or inactive. (common to mid-block signals)
Set when overlap begins timing red clearance intervals.
Set when overlap has completed all timing, allowing any conflicting phase next to begin service.
Set when overlap head is set dark (no active outputs). The end of this interval shall be recorded by either an overlap off state or other active overlap state.
Set when walk indication becomes active.
Set when flashing don’t walk indication becomes active.

description: Set when don’t walk indication becomes solid (non flashing) from either termination of ped clearance, or head illumination after a ped dark interval.
Set when the pedestrian outputs are set off.
Set when advance warning sign becomes active.
Set when advance warning sign becomes inactive.
Detector on and off events shall be triggered post any detector delay/extension processing.
Detector on and off events shall be triggered post any detector delay/extension processing.
Detector restored to non-failed state by either manual restoration or re-enabling via continued diagnostics.
Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics only (not system diagnostics).
Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics only (not system diagnostics).
Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics only (not system diagnostics).
Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics only (not system diagnostics).
Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics only (not system diagnostics).

Ped detector events shall be triggered post any detector delay/extension processing and may be set multiple times for a single pedestrian call. (with future intent to eventually support ped presence and volume).
Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics only (not system diagnostics).
Detector failure logged upon local controller diagnostics only (not system diagnostics).

TSP detector events shall be triggered post any detector delay/extension processing.
Set when preemption advance warning input is activated.
Set when preemption input is activated. (prior to preemption delay timing) May be set multiple times if input is intermittent during preemption service.
Set when gate down input is received by the controller (if available).
Set when preemption input is de-activated. May be set multiple times if input is intermittent preemption service.
Set when preemption delay expires, and controller begins transition timing (force off) to serve preemption.
Set when track clearance phases are green and track clearance timing begins.
Set when preemption dwell or limited service begins, or minimum dwell timer is reset due to call drop and reapplication.
Set when linked preemptor input is applied from active preemptor.
Set when linked preemptor input is dropped from active preemptor.
Set when preemption max presence timer is exceeded, and preemption input is released from service.
Set when preemption exit interval phases are green and exit timing begins.
Set when request for priority is received.
Set when controller is adjusting active cycle to accommodate early service to TSP phases.
Set when controller is adjusting active cycle to accommodate extended service to TSP phases.
Set when request for priority is retracted.
Set when preemption force off is applied to the active cycle.
Set when TSP early force off is applied to the active cycle.
Set when requested TSP service begins.
Set when requested TSP service ends.

Coordination pattern that is actively running in the controller. (Highest priority of TOD, System or manual command). This event will not be reapplied if coordination is temporarily suspended for preemption or other external control.

This event shall be populated upon selection of a new coordination pattern change that selects a new cycle length. Cycle lengths in excess of 255 shall record this event with a 255 parameter, along with event code 156.

This event shall be populated upon selection of a new coordination pattern change that selects a new cycle length. Offsets in excess of 255 shall record this event with a 255 parameter, requiring controller database lookup for this actual value.

Split change events shall be populated upon selection of a new coordination pattern as well as during a split change to an active pattern via Signal Control and Prioritization (SCP), Adaptive Control System (ACS) Lite or other adaptive control system.

Parameter (0-6) defined as:
 0 = Free
 1 = In Step
 2 = Transition - Add
 3 = Transition - Subtract
 4 = Transition - Dwell 5 = Local Zero
 6 = Begin Pickup
 7 = Master Cycle Zero
Set once per cycle for each coordinated phase when controller suspends the coordinated phase.
Set when coordinated phase begins.
Set when the logic statement evaluation changes from “False” to “True”.
Set when the logic statement evaluation changes from “True” to “False”.

Set simultaneously with Event Code 132 when existing cycle length exceeds 255 seconds. When this Event Code 156 is used, Event Code 132 shall be 255, where the value of this Event Code 156 will be the additional cycle length above 255 (in seconds). Cycle lengths longer than 510 seconds will require a controller look up.

Set when the controller OS clock is adjusted via communications, OS command, or external input.
Line voltage drops between 0-89 volts AC for more than 100ms.
Line voltage applied/reapplied greater than 98 volts AC.
